rComments: It is a great shame for DPES at UTSC to lose such an amazing lecturer! She was very inspiring, caring, genius, and  enthusiasm about her job. I am sure that the  department of physical and environmental sciences at U of T at Scarborough campus  did not deserve such an amazing  scholar! She was simply the smartest chemist at this department!
Simply BEST EVER PROFFFFF at UTSC :)
One of those professors who cares about your future!Best  Prof and mentor at UTSC

One of the nicest profs I have ever met at UTSC! She really loves to get to know her students, she genuinely cares about them and wants them to succeed in the course.  Her exams are pretty easy: a few calculations but mostly straight up memorizing. Highly recommend taking one of her classes.
She is a great lecturer and amazing mentor, I have ever seen at UTSC.  I want to get more courses with her!! Love her!
I have CHMB16 with her, she is simply amazing!I will take more courses with her and recommend her :) Her lectures are amazing, clear and she is a great mentor.
Terrible Prof. Unclear. Does not listen to feedback. Very disrespectful towards students. Expects you to learn everything on your own. Do not take CHMB41 with her!!
Amazing prof! Gives a lot of sample problems, goes through them which help a lot for the tests and final. Best chem prof at utsc.

Great lectures! Her slides are clear to learn, she goes through many sample problems which help you to learn the concept deeply and get ready to ace your exam! Wish she was teaching CHMA10 in Summer, I CHMA10 in Winter 2015
Great instructor! I am looking forward to get CHMA11 with her
Incredibly intelligent and organized educator. There are no surprises - she outlines exactly what she will teach you and exactly what she wants from you. Incredibly approachable!

Her sample questions and practice questions she gave us were very helpful in passing the exam. Some of those questions she gave us would be in the exam as well so it wouldn't be some surprise question that you've never seen.

rComments: Awesome !!!! Her exams are very fair, I just did what she told us to do and got A+

Prof. Fathi's dedication often goes unrecognized but she is a very committed instructor! She puts lots of effort to make the classes and labs understandable for students while still encouraging students to think beyond what is presented.

Fathi is a good prof she is very clear, I don't understand why students dislike her. I personally found her very helpful! her midterms are easy but the finals are harder. However as long as you do the required readings and the questions she posted you can achieve a easy AB.

Fari teaches with a good pace and makes sure all students understand the materials very well. She interacts effectively with students and let them raise their questions in the class. I will take more courses with her!

Professor Fari was a very good professor overall. As a first year , it was especially helpful that she provided a ton of sample problems that she clearly explained and went over. Midterm was super easy.  Didn't answer my office hour questions, said she would later but never did, but I only had 2 on one occasion.
I love her teaching style. Clear, concise and many samplr and practice problems which help to understand concepts and get a good grade! Amazing younge Prof :)

She is very clear about the test form and teaches very well. She solves sample problems for each new concept which she teaches and provides us practice and extra problem set. I take more courses with her!
talks very quickly and tries to get through quickly

rComments: Awesome lecturer! solves sample problems which help a lot for getting a good grade.
Excellent Instructor!
Had her for two courses and she was a great prof. Hopefully she teaches C level courses as well.
Simply Awesomeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeee!
She solves many sample problems which help to ace the exam. Her slides are clear and well-prepared. If you want to get a good grade attend to the class and practice given problems.

Prof. Fathi is known to work through mannnnnnnnny questions in class, all for the benefit of the students! As she always emphasizes, those questions are representative of what she would ask on a testexam. She could easily just assign the questions as homework but instead, she takes the time to solve them step-by-step.

This course is very tough; however, she made it very understandable with solving lots of problems during her lectures. She is very helpful for doing assignments and assists students to ace their exams. I strongly recommend taking this course with her.

This course is a tough course; however, she made it easy by clear explanation and solving many problems during her lectures. She was very helpful for doing assignments and helped a lot to do very well on exams.  I strongly recommend taking course

If you work hard and try to enjoy the content, the course becomes more and more interesting. The lectures were easy to follow and the material is not impossible, just requires some practice!  Prof. Fathi is approachable & helpful!

rComments: Attend to the lectures, understand the materials and do the homework by yourself and you get a high grade.
Prof. Fathi always tries to give extra help and provide opportunities to ask questions. She tries to accommodate everyone. I found the course enjoyable despite the difficulty of the material.

Very dedicated and passionate towards chemistry, you can see it through her lectures and real-world examples. Prof. Fathi tries to make the material relevant and understandable to students. She is always available for extra help after class and during her office hours. The notes are well organized and clear.

She is a very approachable and friendly prof! Just put in your share of hard work for this already HARD course which she teaches VERY WELL! I was generally impressed and she was a very test maker and a fair midterm as well!

Very poor prof in general. Gets frustrated with you if you have any questions or require a more in depth explanation. Rushes through material and expects you to understand when she does not explain essential concepts. Marking is fairly lenient however and tests are fair, nevertheless avoid if you can.
Extremely rude when a student asks her questions. So unclear regarding the material. The book is more useful. Avoid her class if you can.
if you could, avoid it
In response to the prev comment: I have been to Prof. Fathi's office hours many times and she has always opened her door right on time, not late.

She simply doesn't explain all the concepts well, though they will be tested on. Rushes through a lot of material. There is a lot of material in general, but she should provide proper explanations for the main concepts. She was also very late to her office hours. Generally, unimpressed with her.
AWFUL! Extremely unhelpful and very rude. Not understanding at all.

Prof. Fathi transforms intimidating classes into more manageable topics. She tries to explain concepts in multiple ways to help us understand. I found the extra problem sets and the clicker questions to be especially helpful too. ) As a lab coordinator, Prof. Fathi was always available during the labs & office hours to answer any questions.

Fari is really nice and helpful. She an incredible teacher who cares about all students. She may look intimidating at the first look, but she is not and can be one of your fiends. Her exams are fair and she solves a lot of sample questions in the class which help students to get a good mark. I strongly recommend her.

the prof should definitely get more credit, she really does care about how we do on the exams and about our futures. yes, the course is tough itself and she has to cover A LOT of material within the limited time in the semester, but that's not her fault. she gives a lot of practice questions (i.e. h.w questions and heck a lot of clicker questions)!

rComments: Avoid taking it if you have her, but it you have no choice then make sure you go to class (clicker questions are for marks) &  the labs are Pretty easy so do well on those. Exams are fine, and take opportunities to do any extra credit or extra mark things she gives. The course overall is not to be hated, its fairly easy. This prof tho is just bad.

Tried to make the course material interesting by giving examples in the industry. A very knowledgeable prof in organic and phys chem. She often encourages class participation and questions, making sure we understand. The lecture slides and notes were in line with the textbook, making it easy to follow up!

Very helpful in her office hours; will give more examples, help with assignment questions, and learns names! Lectures are good because there are many examples solved in class. She also leaves some questions for us to do as extra practice. Overall a friendly prof, I respect her!

The professor claims to appreciate questions and participation by students during lecture times, yet manages to be condescending to questions asked by dismissing them as easy and answering very briefly. the worst prof i ever had, unclear, really hard to following her lecture, and textbook will become ur best friend. she is very very very rude, alway like ignore questions u asked on class. never take her class, totally a nightmare.

Fathi is a great Prof and make Organic Chem easy to understand. She tells you exactly what you need to know to do well on her exams. I do not know what the other comments are talking about as Fathi is very respectful and nice. Go to her office hours guys!
